## Definition 

A morphism of [[affine schemes]] $Spec A \to Spec B$ is _pro-Ã©tale_ if it is a [[filtered limit]] of [[Ã©tale morphisms of schemes]] over $Spec B$, dually if $B \to A$ is an [[ind-object|ind-]][[Ã©tale algebra]].

Pro Ã©tale morphisms into some [[scheme]] $X$ form the [[pro-Ã©tale site]] of $X$.

